{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"Included with: <b> θαυμ-αστός</b>, <br /> <i>Ionic dialect</i> <b>θωμ-</b>, ή, όν, <b>wonderful, marvellous</b>, first in <i>neuter</i> as <i>adverb</i>, θαυμαστὸν γανόωντα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “hymnus ad Cererem” 10 \">Refs</a>]; ἔργα μεγάλα καὶ θ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1 “Prooem.”; θ. καρπός [prev. author] 9.122 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; θ. λόχος γυναικῶν, of the Furies, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 46; οὐδὲν τούτων θαυμαστὸν ἐμοί 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 191, etc.; ὃ πάντων -ότατον 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Symposium” 220a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; θ. πλέγμα, in Medicine texts, the <b>rete mirabile</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 5.196: with _accusative_, θαυμαστὴ τὸ κάλλος 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 110c; πᾶσαν ἀρετήν [prev. author] “Lg.” 945e: with _genitive_, τῆς εὐσταθείας 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Publicola” 14; τῆς ἐπιεικείας [prev. author] “Per.” 39: with _dative_, πλήθει [prev. author] “Caes.” 6; πλέοσι ἐσόμεθα θωμαστότεροι 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 9.122; πρός τι 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.980d: followed by an _interrogative_, εἰ, etc., θαυμαστὸν ὅσον.. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], Latin <i>mirum quantum</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 150d, etc.; θαυμαστὸν ἡλίκον 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 24.122; θαυμαστά γ᾽, εἰ.. 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Symposium” 4.3 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; οὐδὲν θ., εἰ.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 279a, “R.” 390a; οὐ δὴ θ., εἰ.. 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 2.23 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]. <i>adverb</i> <b>-τῶς</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 633b; θαυμαστῶς ὡς σφόδρα [prev. author]